==Fight overview==
[[File:Fighting General Graardor.png|thumb|250px|A group of players fighting General Graardor and his minions.]]
{{Main|General Graardor/Strategies}}
Like other God Wars Dungeon bosses, Graardor roams around a rectangular room with his bodyguards until a player enters, attacking them on sight. He attacks primarily with [[melee]] (2/3 chance{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/689065027844878338|date=17 January 2016|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/0LEUP|archivedate=29 March 2019|quote=2/3 melee, 1/3 "ranged".|name=attack chance}}), and his bodyguards use a different combat style each. Graardor may also use a [[ranged]] attack (1/3 chance{{NamedRef|attack chance}}) where he slams the ground, hitting all players in the room which has an equal chance to hit between 15-35 upon successfully hitting the player{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1054823168559538177|date=23 October 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/USdjg|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=[Graardor's ranged attack is] rolling 15-35 inclusive, with equal chances for each of those 21 numbers.}}. If there are no players in his chamber, his health and stats will be reset.

===Bodyguards===
*[[Sergeant Strongstack]] ([[Melee]])
*[[Sergeant Steelwill]] ([[Magic]])
*[[Sergeant Grimspike]] ([[Ranged]])

==Quotes==
General Graardor will yell out the following whether or not he is in combat with any players:
*"Death to our enemies!"
*"Brargh!"
*"Break their bones!"
*"Split their skulls!"
*"We feast on the bones of our enemies tonight!"
*"CHAAARGE!"
*"Crush them underfoot!"
*"All glory to Bandos!"
*"GRRRAAAAAR!"
*"For the glory of the Big High War God!"

